title: Sybil Vane
description: Sybil Vane is a sentiment analysis tool designed to detect media bias in real-time events using Python and spaCy's NLP models. It leverages JSON dictionaries to store and analyze over 350 articles and 560,000 words, optimizing named entity recognition through a custom training algorithm.

title: Market Vision
description: Developed a financial analysis model leveraging pandas to evaluate and score 30 active stocks daily based on technical and fundamental criteria. Enhanced efficiency by optimizing OpenAI API integration, reducing costs by 98.5% through refined data organization and training methodologies.

title: Computer Vision Applications
description: Executed computer vision and image transformation tasks using pre-trained neural and cycle-GAN networks in PyTorch. Structured over 700 multi-dimensional data batches with NumPy and integrated ImageNet's extensive dataset to enhance model accuracy and functionality.

title: Rilke Analytics
description: Developed AI-driven tools to enhance student learning by incorporating reflection intervals and targeted weakness identification through custom-trained Natural Entity Recognition models. Inspired by Rainer Maria Rilke Letters to a Young Poet, the approach fosters thoughtful and personalized study optimization.
